 lung is characterized by a cascade of avalanches, as the airways successively open, and that distribution functions characterizing this cascade are scale invariant. Moving from the lung to the heart, we find that the sequence of interbeat intervals is characterized by scale-invariant correlations in health, but not in disease. Moving from individual organs to entire organisms, we discuss recent experimental evidence that the foraging behaviour of the wandering albatross is governed by a scale-invariant Levy distribution. Finally,...","publicationCount":0,"publicationCountByYear":[],"citationCnt":10,"citationCountByYear":[],"rank":21649.0,"entityType":0},"dataVersion":"2019-01-11-prod"}